product_name: CliniqueClinique Smart Clinical Repair Wrinkle Correcting Face Cream
summary: SummaryHighlightsSustainable PackagingClinique Smart Clinical Repair Wrinkle Correcting Face Cream is a wrinkle-fighting moisturizer that helps strengthen and nourish for smoother, younger-looking skin.
details: DetailsBenefitsAll Skin TypesAnti-wrinkle face cream strengthens, visibly repairs lines and wrinkles, hydrates.A powerful addition to Clinique's most advanced de-aging line yet, Clinique Smart Clinical Repair, this ultra-nourishing moisturizer is engineered to visibly reduce lines and wrinkles for supple, younger-looking skin.Cutting-edge formula with CL1870 Peptide Complex helps boost skin's natural collagen to help fortify the dermal structure, leaving skin feeling stronger and looking smoother.Moisturizer plumps skin with lasting hydration, which helps minimize the appearance of fine, dry lines.Available in two textures: Wrinkle Correcting Cream is a lightweight cream for All Skin Types and Wrinkle Correcting Rich Cream is a luxe, denser cream for those with drier skin.Built on Dermatological Science: As a dermatologist-guided brand, Clinique's commitment to safety starts with skincare science. Clinique partners with the best minds in dermatology and formulate for all skin types, tones, concerns - in service of all skin.Fragrance-free, Paraben-free, Phthalate-free, Oil-free, Free of synthetic colors.More Responsible Packaging:50ml and 15ml jars each contain a minimum of 30% post-consumer recycled content.Carton is made from responsibly sourced paperboard. Please recycle.Safe for sensitive skinAllergy TestedFragrance freeKey IngredientsPowered by peptides, this anti-wrinkle face cream helps strengthen skin and visibly repair lines and wrinkles.CL1870 Peptide Complex: An expert peptide blend engineered to fight the look of wrinkles by boosting natural collagen, which helps strengthen skin's natural support structure.Hyaluronic acid: Exclusive formula uses two molecular weights of hyaluronic acid. This intense humectant helps flood your skin with hydration -and holds on. Helps restore suppleness and visibly smooth fine, dry lines.Soybean seed extract: An ingredient rich in lysophosphatidic acid (LPA), which nourishes to help fortify skin.Leveraging Clinique's 35 years of peptide expertise, formula includes ''self-assembly,'' ''neuropeptide,'' and ''signaling peptides:''Palmitoyl tripeptide-1Acetyl hexapeptide-8Palmitoyl tetrapeptide-7Palmitoyl hexapeptide-12Research ResultsSensory testing (applies only to the Cream formula for All Skin Types):After 1 use, 91% of 148 women say skin looks smoother and feels firmer.After 1 week:95% of 148 women say skin feels hydrated throughout the day.95% say skin feels hydrated throughout the night.After 4 weeks:92% of 146 women say skin feels firmer.92% of 146 women say skin looks smoother.93% of 146 women say neck feels smoother.94% of 146 women say skin looks healthier.85% of 143 women say lines and wrinkles look reduced.Item 2598026How To UseUse moisturizer twice a day, morning and night as part of daily skincare routine.Apply wrinkle cream to face and neck after using Clinique Smart Clinical Repair Wrinkle Correcting Serum.Follow with Clinique Smart Clinical Repair Wrinkle Correcting Eye Cream for the ultimate de-aging routine.Always include SPF sunscreen as the last step in the AM.IngredientsWater\Aqua\Eau, Glycerin, Isostearyl Neopentanoate, Butylene Glycol, Glyceryl Stearate, faceoff_positive.comments:
I'm sincerely thankful too @bzzagent for sending this  #freesample in exchange for my honest opinion.  I received @clinique Smart Clinical Repair Wrinkle Correcting Cream and incorporated into my current skincare regimen for a full 7 days. Please continue reading about my results & findings as I share #nixtwocents - This cream is described as a light weight wrinkle-fighting cream that helps strengthen and nourish for smoother, younger-looking skin. It's recommended for all skin types and twice daily use once in AM & PM - Package claims include dermatologist tested, allergy tested, and 100% fragrance free. The following are a few of the key ingredients & the results Clinique claimes this cream produces. 
CL1870 Peptide Complex is an expert peptide blend engineered to fight the look of wrinkles by boosting natural collagen, which helps strengthen skin's natural support structure. 
Hyaluronic acid in two molecular weights is an intense humectant that helps flood your skin with hydration and holds on; it helps restore suppleness and visibly smooth fine, dry lines.
Soybean seed extract is rich in lysophosphatidic acid (LPA), which nourishes to help fortify skin. The very first time I applied this cream to my face I immediately noticed an obvious chemical odor that dissipated as the cream absorbed. It made me leary about the 100% fragrance free claim. I used approximately a dime size amount & was able to cover my entire face / neck area. I do think this cream is more on the heavier side when It comes to absorption as it took a full 5 minutes to absorb. Eventhough it left my skin feeling nourished & hydrated it also left me with a greasy, shiny residue because it never did fully absorb. It was this reason I decided this cream is better suited as a once daily use part of my PM regimen. After a full week of use, overall I'm pleased with my results. My face felt moisturized, replenished, and my skin appears to look smoother. I havn't noticed any diminished fine lines or wrinkles. I believe those results would require more time & usage. I have always enjoyed Clinique products and I honestly think this Clinique Smart Clinical Repair Wrinkle Correcting Cream should be considered a night Cream. I recommend you conduct your own trial run and see if you get the same results I did. I wouldn't count this one out but I also can't say it won me over. #bzzagent #freesample #nixtwocents #cliniquesmartclinicalrepair
faceoff_positive.headline: More like a night cream

faceoff_negative.comments:
I received a sample to try, which I greatly appreciate.  Perhaps this is just not for me.  I am mixed race, so I get to try *ALL THE THINGS*...often for decades...before someone starts coming up with products that seem to work for our unique skin and hair. (or perhaps, a more precise way to see it is...  *our hair and skin*, but long overlooked as worth focusing on to major cosmetic companies, so *TaDaaa* we now end up being the hard to find products for version of *unique* when it comes to suitable products (I mean, unique is as it does...but that's an individual thing).  After all that, add on that I'm in a "big changes" phase.  And my skin has decided that it's going to start the adult ageing process as of the last 3 years...sort of making up for people always saying I looked "...25...maybe 27?" until I turned 41.  So take that into account.
As to feel, it took a while before it absorbed.  Then it did almost instantly.  It isn't specifically a moisturizer, and to my embarrassment I never looked up the product information (ingredients, individual ingredient properties vs. combined product claims and goals), but a wrinkle focused product with no moisture mention on label makes me think it is mainly a wrinkle filler (again, could be wrong).  But this doesn't feel like it moisturises my skin.  Even though it absorbed enough to not be just wiped off of my skin, it felt like it was sitting right on top (which, perhaps, is normal in a filler product).  I continued to use this product, both on my face and specifically on my left back of the hand (I am curious, I haven't used wrinkle products much yet, and I wanted to see if I noticed any changes), so I could easily check it out through the day.  I really haven't noticed much difference over the course of the sample's contents.   Not on my hand or face, at this point in my life/skin ageing.
faceoff_negative.headline: Perhaps this is just not for me.
